1. Python Basics  
   - Data types, Operators, String formatting, Type conversion  
   - Control statements (if-else, loops), List, Dict, Tuple, Set  

2. Functions & Modules  
   - def, return, *args, **kwargs, Scope (LEGB), Lambda functions  
   - map(), filter(), reduce(), Importing modules, __name__  

3. OOP (Object-Oriented Programming)  
   - Classes, Objects, __init__, self, Encapsulation, Inheritance  
   - Polymorphism, Abstract classes, Method Overloading/Overriding  

4. Exception Handling  
   - try-except-finally, raise, Custom exceptions  

5. File Handling  
   - open(), read(), write(), File modes, with statement  

6. Advanced Python  
   - List/Dict Comprehensions, Generators, Iterators, Decorators  
   - yield vs return, Multithreading vs Multiprocessing  

7. Data Structures & Algorithms  
   - Lists, Tuples, Sets, Dictionaries, Stacks, Queues, Linked Lists  
   - Sorting (Bubble, Merge, Quick), Searching (Binary Search), Recursion  

8. Regular Expressions (`re` module)  
   - search(), match(), findall(), sub()  

9. Database Handling  
   - sqlite3, MySQL, PostgreSQL, CRUD operations, ORM (SQLAlchemy)  

10. Web Frameworks  
   - Flask (APIs), Django (MVC, Models, Views, Templates)  

11. Unit Testing  
   - unittest, Mocking, Patching  

12. Logging & Debugging  
   - logging module, Debugging using pdb  

13. Python for Data Science (Optional)  
   - NumPy, Pandas, Matplotlib, Data Analysis  

14. Python in Cloud & DevOps (Optional)  
   - AWS (Boto3), Docker, Kubernetes, CI/CD  
